            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/acpi/video_detect.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"video_detect_dmi_table\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c. By default, the system incorrectly selects acpi_backlight_vendor (acer_wmi driver) which doesn't work on this device. The device should default to acpi_backlight_native (intel_backlight driver) instead, which works correctly with 15-16 brightness levels. The fix requires adding an entry to video_detect_dmi_table with the video_detect_force_native callback to properly match this system based on its DMI identifiers (Acer TravelMate 5735Z with board name BA51_MV). This is confirmed by the fact that using the kernel parameter acpi_backlight=native works correctly on this device.\"\n}\n",
